cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.ET, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the design of autonomous sensor networks, which involves networking and communication aspects. 
2. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes an energy management framework for self-sufficient sensor networks, which involves control and optimization aspects. 
3. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper deals with the design of distributed sensor networks, which involves computing and data processing aspects. 
4. cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) - The paper discusses the use of renewable energy sources for powering sensor networks, which is an emerging technology. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper evaluates the performance of the proposed energy management policies in terms of network throughput and battery level dynamics.
